{"word":"αἰθήρ","slug":"αἰθήρ","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>αἰθήρ</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:αἴθω'><el>αἴθω</el></a>\n<br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>in <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b> fem; in <b><a href='S:Hesiod'>Hes.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, and attic Prose masc; in <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b> and <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b> masc or <a href='S:feminine'>fem.</a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>ether, the brighter purer air, the sky</i>, above the <el>ἀήρ</el> (<a href='S:quod vide'>q. <a href='S:vide'>v.</a></a>); <el>Ζεὺς αἰθέρι ναίων</el> <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>a clime, region</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}